We took a little long to engage once the MT got aggro and ran a little low on mana.  We succored to zone and ran back.<br>
<br>
During this time, 4 Miracle wizards zoned in.  Sun Tzu Guardians was trying to amass people as well.  One cleric with STG told me they did not have the chanters.  A monk with Sun Tzu (I may be wrong about the guild tag...I'm just going by ooc in zone) managed to aggro VS to zone.  SW had already run back to prep to rez the few that died.  We were medding to full as we waited on  VS to path back.  <br>
<br>
The four Miracle wizzies, walk right past us...this took under 10 minutes from the the time we succored and he was trained to zone btw.... They manaburn him and loot and gate in under 20 seconds.<br>
<br>
Not one tell to me....nor others in  our guild concerning him by Miracle.  I can't really call it KS cause we weren't engaged at the time they walked past.  We were fully buffed and about to pull <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
Although manaburn is so nice to have for when SW needs it (hehe), this time I think it allowed some folks to basically just steal the show.  I believe in being fair.   I believe in open mobs...ie if you don't have the folks there to do it ..not much you can do.  This wasn't the case.  We had the folks.  We were ready to go any second.  We hadn't been there for hours.  What they did was just RUDE.  If you want respect, then show it.<br>
Does this guild not care about its reputation?<br>
<br>
One of the Miracle folks Reon, was an officer.  I tried talking to Reon after he logged back on after gating.  He said SW trained them.  Figures<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I told him this wasn't the case.  I told him what they did was rude. He says to me, I wash my screen or something.....you are now on ignore (talking to the chanter I was playing).  <br>
<br>
<br>
What can you do? /sigh<br>
<br>
<br>
Tiriella<br>
Guild Leader<br>
